  "articleSummary": "The article argues that AngularJS v1.x developers often overuse two-way data binding and directives, leading to performance issues from excessive `$watch` instances and bloated `$scope` hierarchies. It recommends limiting directive nesting, using one-way binding (`::`), and avoiding directives inside `ng-repeat` to improve efficiency. The tone is a practical tutorial with humorous metaphors like \"2-way sword\" and \"OVER-Angular.JSification,\" targeting developers of medium-to-large AngularJS apps. It also suggests Browserify for project organization and briefly compares ReactJS and Polymer as alternatives for UI-heavy projects.",
